Q.1 Apply python program in each of the following transformation on the point p[3,-1].

i)Reflection through x-axis.

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[1,0],[0,-1]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(3,-1)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(3.0, 1.0)

ii)Scalling in x co-ordinate by factor 2.

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[2,0],[0,1]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(3,-1)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(6.0, -1.0)

iii)Scalling in y co-ordinate by factor 1.5 .

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[1,0],[0,1.5]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(3,-1)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(3.0, -1.5)

iv)Reflection through the line y=x.

import numpy as np
import math
 
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[0,1],[1,0]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(3,-1)
ref(point)

OUTPUT:-
(-1.0, 3.0)
