Q.2 Apply python program in each of the following transformation on the point p[4,-2].

i)Reflection through y-axis.

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[-1,0],[0,1]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(4,-2)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(-4.0, -2.0)



ii)Scalling in x co-ordinate by factor 3.

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[3,0],[0,1]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(4,-2)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(12.0, -2.0)

iv)Reflection through y=-x.

import numpy as np
import math
def ref(xy):
    x,y=xy
    j=np.matrix([[0,1],[-1,0]])
    m=np.dot(j,[x,y])
    return float(m.T[0]),float(m.T[1])
point=(4,-2)
ref(point)
OUTPUT:-
(-2.0, -4.0)

